---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Containing AD — Scrabble Word List & Strategy"
  description="Complete list of Scrabble words containing AD with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Find AD words for your next winning play."
  keywords="scrabble words containing ad, ad words scrabble, words with ad, scrabble ad word list, ad scrabble strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Containing AD — Scrabble Word List & Strategy",
    "description": "Complete list of Scrabble words containing AD with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Find AD words for your next winning play.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-ad" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the highest-scoring Scrabble words containing AD?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "High-scoring AD words include ADJUDGE (17 pts), GADFLY (14 pts), SHADOW (13 pts), MADCAP (13 pts), and BADGE (9 pts). The AD pair works well with premium consonants and appears in many longer scoring words." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many valid Scrabble words contain AD?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Over 900 valid Scrabble words contain AD. It is an extremely common pair appearing in everyday words like ADD, BAD, DAD, HAD, MAD, PAD, SAD, and hundreds of longer words like SHADE, TRADE, and ADVANCE." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What 3-letter AD words are useful in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Essential 3-letter AD words include ADD (5 pts), BAD (6 pts), CAD (6 pts), DAD (5 pts), FAD (7 pts), GAD (5 pts), HAD (7 pts), LAD (4 pts), MAD (6 pts), PAD (6 pts), RAD (4 pts), SAD (4 pts), TAD (4 pts), and WAD (7 pts)." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Containing AD — Scrabble Word List & Strategy</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        AD is one of the most prolific letter pairs in Scrabble. The combination appears in nearly every game thanks to abundant A and D tiles (9 As and 4 Ds in the bag). Whether you are playing short tactical words like BAD and PAD, or extending into longer plays like SHADOW and ADVANCE, the AD pair offers consistent scoring potential across all board states.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top AD Words by Score</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ADJUDGE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To rule or decide</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GADFLY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A biting insect</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SHADOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A dark silhouette</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MADCAP</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Recklessly impulsive</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SHADE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Partial darkness</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BADGE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">An identifying emblem</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HAD</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Past tense of have</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">WAD</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A lump of material</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">FAD</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A temporary trend</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GRADE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A level or rank</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TRADE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">An exchange of goods</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">900+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid AD words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Average score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Very Common</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Pair rarity</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Short AD Words for Every Situation</h2>

      <p>The -AD ending accepts nearly every consonant in front of it, giving you a massive arsenal of 3-letter plays for tight board positions.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">BAD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">CAD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">FAD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">HAD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">MAD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">PAD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">WAD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Key Takeaway</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AD words are <span class="text-white font-medium">everywhere in Scrabble</span>. The -AD ending accepts almost any consonant prefix (BAD, CAD, FAD, GAD, HAD, LAD, MAD, PAD, RAD, SAD, TAD, WAD), making it one of the most flexible patterns. Use short AD words to score while setting up longer plays like SHADE and TRADE.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-qu" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-multiple-vowels" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words With Multiple Vowels — Scrabble Vowel Dumps</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/four-letter-words-every-player-should-know" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Four-Letter Words Every Scrabble Player Should Know</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every AD word from your tiles — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
